cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this paper, please cite it as below."
title: "Coding-Tuned LLM Variants Produce Version-Specific Stylistic Shifts Within a Shared Essayistic Register: A Marker-Level Analysis Across Z.ai GLM and OpenAI Codex Pairs"
abstract: >
  Major LLM labs increasingly ship coding-tuned variants alongside their
  general-tier models. We ask whether these variants produce a
  systematically different stylistic signature from their general-line
  siblings on freely-prompted (non-coding) output, using the v2
  Convergent Form, Divergent Voice corpus shared with two companion
  papers. We compare six general/coding pairs from two labs: Z.ai
  GLM-4.6 and GLM-5.1 (general side pinned to the lab's own upstream
  via OpenRouter provider.only=z-ai at n=120-125) and OpenAI gpt-5.0 /
  5.1 / 5.2 / 5.3 each paired with their codex sibling (both via
  direct API, three independent rounds of n=25 pooled to n=75 per
  cell). The composite-level direction is not consistent across the
  six pairs. The marker-level finding is more important than the
  composite, and most pairs share a register. Five of the six pairs
  share a base register (essayistic-meditative within the
  contemplative-essayist basin) on both general and coding sides; the
  coding cells differ from their general siblings via marker density,
  length, structural scaffolding, sub-vehicle, or thematic re-routing
  rather than via a register migration. One pair (GPT-5.3) produces a
  clean register migration: declarative-fabular parable to
  atmospheric-essayistic reflection, stable across all three rounds.
  One pair (GPT-5.1) shows a round-1 register excursion to third-person
  fabulist that is the qualitative twin of that round's composite-171
  outlier and does not persist to rounds 2 and 3. There is no shared
  "codex stylistic shift" across pairs - each version's coding-tuning
  pipeline produces its own marker-level signature. Triple-collection
  across the OpenAI cells reveals that single-round n=25 measurements
  on coding-tuned cells are not reliable per-cell coordinates;
  between-round std-dev is itself the diagnostic.
